ned Changes to Improve Safety

Chlorine System

In September 1994, the chlorine system was thoroughly examined for safety hazards by way of a Process Hazard Analysis (PHA).  In addition, PHA Revalidations were conducted in March 1999, June 2004, February 2009, January 2014, December 2018, and April 2024.  The April 2024 PHA Revalidation consisted of:

-	A review of the PHA Requirements / History (Overview / Training Session);
-	A detailed review of the recommended action items from 2018 PHA Revalidation Study; 
-	An equipment list review;
-	A detailed review of any changes to the chlorine system since the 2018 study (reviewed Management of Change Records);
-	A discussion of any releases of chlorine since the 2018 study (review of Incident Investigation Records);
-	Development of HAZOP log sheets;
-	Completion of Emergency Response, Chlorine Checklist, Chlorine What-If Questions, and External Events checklists; and
-	A facility inspection.

The mitigation measures included enhanced emergency response and operating procedures. 

Aqueous Ammonia System

Mitigation measures to prevent accidents involving aqueous ammonia include additional training, key maintenance related tests/inspection, and enhanced emergency response policies and procedures. The Sweetwater Authority safety review committee is planning to meet annually, as a continual effort to provide a safe work environment for their employees.  These changes include the following items:

1. 	Continue to train all employees in the facility Safety Plan/Programs.
2. 	Continue to have employee involvement in Safety Plan Development.
3. 	Continue employee involvement through safety team participation.
4. 	Continue internal and external safety audits/inspections and implement changes as needed.
